Laka Strolistandiler wrote:
Imperial-Octavia wrote:Nuclear mines? Like in the ground?

Laka is extremely serious about it’s defense. Nuclear mines are basically wire-detonated (or, in case of high-yield weapons person-detonated) nuclear weapons dug into the ground. High-yields are essentially nukes with people who will activate them and blow up on them. Pretty much an ICBM without a launch system. But hey at very least if an enemy manages to get through we can keep nuking him even without actually having to worry about delivery systems! Strategic nuking your own lands, what can possibly go wrong!

ik you're being sarcastic, but I would like to point out the logistics anyways.

Provided that said said nukes are of average yield (Roughly 300 kilotons, using the Minuteman III as an example), this would be disastrous for any region even if you're trying to take out a large army. The most isolated spot in Britain (as a random example of how a European country would be affected) is the Southwest, otherwise known as Cornwall. If an army detonated a mine at Millbrook in order to "defend" the city of Plymouth, well - there wouldn't be much of a Plymouth to defend anymore. Thermal heat hot enough to cause skin and wood to catch fire would ingulf most of the city, even from 6 1/2 kilometers away. Given how this is a technically ground burst, it gets worse. On a good day, Plymouth and surrounding towns like Exter would be subject to radiation (~1,000 rads per hour) high enough to kill within hours if not minutes. On a bad day, radiation enough to kill 50% of the human population would cover the vast majority of Cornwall. This would leave roughly 600,000 people dead in a bad (but still not worse case) scenario. Aaaand, that's in a low-density region. If a mine went off in Margate and the wind conditions went to London, it could kill 5 million - possibly more seeing how the statistics I was using came from a 2015 census. So unless your nation is as thinly-packed as Mongolia, the size of Russia, or both - it would more-or-less be suicide for the nation whilst only moderately harming the invading army. Even then, rendering a region in need of humanitarian aid and its infrastructure unusable is a very short-term solution for a long-term problem such as war.

Was this rant meaningless? Probably. But I saw a reason to nerd about why not to wank nukes in RPs and I jumped on it. /s
